ciscoTelnetServerMIB.name: ciscoTelnetServerMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoTelnetServerMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553 -NETS E-mail: cs-san@cisco.com, cs-lan-switch-snmp@cisco.com
ciscoTelnetServerMIB.description: MIB module for displaying and configuring Telnet related features in a device. Telnet is a program to log into another computer over a network, to execute commands in a remote machine.

ctsTelnetActivation.name: ctsTelnetActivation
ctsTelnetActivation.description: This object specifies whether the Telnet access service on the device is enabled.

ctsSessionEndedNotifEnable.name: ctsSessionEndedNotifEnable
ctsSessionEndedNotifEnable.description: This object controls whether the system produces ctsSessionEnded notifications. A 'false' value will prevent ctsSessionEnded notifications from being generated by this system.

ctsSessionStartedNotifEnable.name: ctsSessionStartedNotifEnable
ctsSessionStartedNotifEnable.description: This object controls whether the system produces ctsSessionStarted notifications. A 'false' value will prevent ctsSessionStarted notifications from being generated by this system.

ctsSessionDeniedNotifEnable.name: ctsSessionDeniedNotifEnable
ctsSessionDeniedNotifEnable.description: This object controls whether the system produces ctsSessionDenied notifications. A 'false' value will prevent ctsSessionDenied notifications from being generated by this system.

ctsSessionFailureNotifEnable.name: ctsSessionFailureNotifEnable
ctsSessionFailureNotifEnable.description: This object controls whether the system produces ctsSessionLoginFailure notifications. A 'false' value will prevent ctsSessionLoginFailure notifications from being generated by this system.

ctsSessionsTable.name: ctsSessionsTable
ctsSessionsTable.description: This table provides data for each telnet session on an entity capable of running telnet server.

ctsSessionsEntry.name: ctsSessionsEntry
ctsSessionsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the ctsSessionsTable. This entry lists the data for the telnet session on the entity running the telnet server. An entry in the ctsSessionTable, that provides detailed information about all the existing telnet sessions on the device. An entry will be created for every telnet session established on the device. The entry will be removed upon termination of the telnet session.

ctsSessionID.name: ctsSessionID
ctsSessionID.description: An arbitrary index that uniquely identifies a Telnet Session.

ctsSessionDescription.name: ctsSessionDescription
ctsSessionDescription.description: Human readable description about the session.

ctsSessionClientAddressType.name: ctsSessionClientAddressType
ctsSessionClientAddressType.description: The type of Internet address of the client that requested this session.

ctsSessionsClientAddress.name: ctsSessionsClientAddress
ctsSessionsClientAddress.description: The Internet address of the client that requested this session. The type of this address is determined by the value of the ctsSessionClientAddressType object.

ctsSessionPID.name: ctsSessionPID
ctsSessionPID.description: The object indicates the process ID of the process serving this telnet session on the device.

ctsSessionUserID.name: ctsSessionUserID
ctsSessionUserID.description: The object indicates user name associated with this telnet session.

ctsSessionTcpPort.name: ctsSessionTcpPort
ctsSessionTcpPort.description: The TCP source port number of the remote client.

ctsSessionEnded.name: ctsSessionEnded
ctsSessionEnded.description: This notification signifies that the agent entity has detected end of a telnet session.

ctsSessionStarted.name: ctsSessionStarted
ctsSessionStarted.description: This notification is sent when the agent entity has accepted a new telnet session.

ctsSessionDenied.name: ctsSessionDenied
ctsSessionDenied.description: This notification signifies that the agent has refused a telnet session.

ctsSessionLoginFailure.name: ctsSessionLoginFailure
ctsSessionLoginFailure.description: This notification is sent when the agent entity has detected attempt to login with wrong credentials.

ciscoTelnetServerMIBCompliance.name: ciscoTelnetServerMIBCompliance
ciscoTelnetServerMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP Agents which implement this MIB.

ctsMIBSessionsObjectGroup.name: ctsMIBSessionsObjectGroup
ctsMIBSessionsObjectGroup.description: This group of objects maintains informative data for each Telnet session on a device that runs Telnet Server.

ctsMIBNotificationGroup.name: ctsMIBNotificationGroup
ctsMIBNotificationGroup.description: This group contains notifications for this MIB.

ctsSessionNotifsControlGroup.name: ctsSessionNotifsControlGroup
ctsSessionNotifsControlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing configuration information applicable to all session notifications.
